{
  "texts": [
    "In addition, the inherent bias in LLM training data [66,106] can lead to the propagation of stereotypical, discriminatory, or biased viewpoints.",
    "This bias can also give rise to hallucinations, where LLMs produce erroneous or misleading information [105,131].",
    "Hallucinations also may stem from overfitting the training data or a lack of context understanding [134].",
    "Such inaccuracies can have serious consequences, such as providing incorrect medical information, reinforcing harmful stereotypes, or failing to recognize and appropriately respond to mental health crises [131].",
    "For example, an LLM might reinforce a harmful belief held by a user, potentially exacerbating their mental health issues, or it could generate non-factual, overly optimistic, or pessimistic medical advice, delaying appropriate professional intervention."
  ]
}